      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): improve error message when node:sqlite is unavailable",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Rebased the existing PR head onto current `upstream/main` and kept the diff scoped to `extensions/memory-core`.\n- Classify `node:sqlite` / missing built-in sqlite runtime errors in `buildMemorySearchUnavailableResult(error, overrides?)`.\n- Keep the existing quota and generic branches, and keep explicit `warning` / `action` overrides authoritative.\n\n## Behavior\n\nWhen the runtime cannot load `node:sqlite`, `memory_search` now returns the same unavailable result shape with a targeted warning/action instead of the generic embedding-provider message.\n\nThe action matches current OpenClaw support policy: Node.js `>=22.19.0`, with Node.js 24 recommended. The doc link uses the valid Memory CLI page: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/memory.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nLocal runtime reproduction on the old Node line:\n\n```text\n$ node -e \"try { require('node:sqlite'); console.log('node:sqlite available'); } catch (error) { console.log(error.code + ': ' + error.message); }\"\nERR_UNKNOWN_BUILTIN_MODULE: No such built-in module: node:sqlite\n```\n\nSupported runtime check:\n\n```text\n$ npx -y node@24 -e \"try { require('node:sqlite'); console.log(process.version + ': node:sqlite available'); } catch (error) { console.log(error.code + ': ' + error.message); }\"\nv24.16.0: node:sqlite available\n```\n\nTargeted test run:\n\n```text\n$ npx -y -p node@24 -p pnpm@11.2.2 pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-memory.config.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       19 passed (19)\n```\n\n## Related\n\n- Supersedes #59637\n- Closes #59457",
